<TITLE> Court orders arrest of Delwar's son Paban </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 30 (bdnews24.com) -- A Dhaka court Tuesday issued an order to arrest Khandaker Akhter Hamid Paban, son of BNP leader Khandaker Delwar Hossain, in a carjacking case. Magistrate SM Moyeen Uddin of the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court for Dhaka issued the warrant. Tuesday was scheduled for framing charges in the case against Paban and his associates Abdul Halim and Zahirul Islam Rabin. Paban's lawyer Gazi Touhidul Islam appealed to the court seeking exemption for his client for a fourth time to appear in court as he was "sick". The lawyer submitted a medical certificate to the court. Quoting the medical certificate, the lawyer said Paban has been suffering from hypertension and jaundice from October 25. The magistrate turned down the appeal and issued the warrant of arrest. According to case details, Paban's associates on October 13, 2005 stole a car of businessman Kazi Mizanur Rahman, which was parked in front of Amin Court in Motijheel. Security forces retrieved the car and arrested him. A case was filed with Motijheel Police Station. Police submitted a chargesheet in the case on December 28, 2006. Paban received bail from the High Court in the case on December 28, 2006. bdnew
